Phase 3: Strategy Builder & Backtesting
3.1 — Form-Based Strategy Builder

Indicator selection: dropdown (SMA, EMA, RSI, MACD, Bollinger, ATR, Pivots, custom)
Entry conditions: form rows — "When [indicator A] [crosses above / > / < / etc.] [indicator B / value]", AND/OR logic
Exit conditions: same structure, plus TP/SL (fixed, ATR multiple, %), trailing stop, time exit
Risk management: position sizing (fixed lot, % risk), max positions, max drawdown stop
Filters: time-of-day, day-of-week, volatility
Strategy saved as JSON in DB
Indicator → Strategy converter: pick indicator, define signal conditions, auto-generate config

3.2 — Backtest Engine (Tick-Level)

Bar-by-bar loop (tick-by-tick when tick data available)
Order simulation: market fills at next open, limit fills on price cross
Slippage + spread + commission models
Position tracking: open/close, partial close, breakeven
Multi-symbol support
Results: equity curve, trade list, stats (win rate, PF, max DD, Sharpe, Sortino, expectancy)
WebSocket progress for long runs
POST /api/backtest/run

3.3 — Backtest Results UI

Equity curve chart, trade markers on price chart
Stats dashboard cards
Trade log table (sortable)
Monthly returns heatmap, drawdown chart
Compare multiple runs side-by-side


Phase 4: Optimization & ML
4.1 — Optimization Engine

UI: define param ranges (numeric min/max/step, categorical options)
Optuna (TPE Bayesian) for efficient search + DEAP (genetic) for broad exploration
Hybrid: Optuna narrows regions → DEAP refines
Walk-forward validation (in-sample optimize, out-of-sample validate)
Results: param importance, optimization history, best params + OOS performance
POST /api/optimize/run with WebSocket progress

4.2 — ML Level 1: Adaptive Parameters

Predict which params work in current market regime
Features: volatility, trend strength, correlation
Model: Random Forest / XGBoost

4.3 — ML Level 2: Signal Prediction

Predict next-bar direction/movement
Features: indicator values, price patterns, volume, time
Models: XGBoost → LSTM → Transformer (progressive)
ML predictions as indicator in strategy builder

4.4 — ML Level 3: Full ML Strategies

End-to-end RL trading agents
Feature store, model registry, A/B testing


